{"author":{"id":"2b4457b01effb9c8da29ce6d2aafea7e87f3ee3dadec9f9fc646e1c6838f70dd"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1634145830,"nonce":"Bcbtvn1kcdj5sDFa2UZ2bKF0oPk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s49IBMv","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4073","origin":"github"},"title":"Kraken2 Data Manager: Links to Minikraken DB are out of date","message":"The [Kraken2 Data Manager](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/tree/master/data_managers/data_manager_build_kraken2_database) includes a feature to download the pre-built 'MiniKraken2' database from an [ftp server hosted at the Johns Hopkins University Center for Computational Biology](https://ccb.jhu.edu/software/kraken2/downloads.shtml).\n\nUnfortunately, the links to the databases that are used in the data manager are no longer resolvable:\n\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/9e5f2fc04f61230208adf2e321ce84cb66e86006/data_managers/data_manager_build_kraken2_database/data_manager/kraken2_build_database.py#L135\n\nThe [Kraken2 homepage](https://ccb.jhu.edu/software/kraken2/) states: \n\n\u003e As of September 2020, we have created a Amazon Web Services site to host many of the most widely-used Kraken2 indices, available at [https://github.com/BenLangmead/aws-indexes](https://benlangmead.github.io/aws-indexes/k2)\n\nThat site provides several pre-built databases, hosted via AWS S3.\n\nCould the Kraken2 data manager be updated to point to the pre-built databases available on Ben Langmead's 'Index Zone' page?","files":null}]}